{"schema_version": 2, "source_hash": "066e1bb748c855a2", "candidate": {"id": "cand-018", "name": "Marcus Webb", "raw_cv": "MARCUS WEBB\nmarcus.webb@email.com | Remote (Edinburgh, UK)\n\nPRODUCT MANAGER\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\nProduct manager with 5 years of experience in SaaS, specialising in integrations and workflow automation products. Strong background in developer-facing products and API strategy.\n\nEXPERIENCE\n\nProduct Manager \u2014 Zapier, Remote (2021\u2013present)\n- PM for the integrations health and reliability product\n- Shipped integration health monitoring dashboard used by 300k+ automation builders\n- Collaborated with 20+ integration partners to define new trigger and action capabilities\n- Partnered with developer relations team on external documentation strategy\n\nProduct Manager \u2014 Typeform, Remote (2019\u20132021)\n- PM for the integrations marketplace\n- Grew native integrations from 40 to 90 in 18 months\n\nSKILLS\nProduct strategy, API products, integrations, developer experience, Amplitude, Jira, Figma, SQL (basic), roadmapping\n\nEDUCATION\nBSc Computer Science \u2014 University of Edinburgh (2014\u20132018)\n\nRIGHT TO WORK\nBritish citizen", "raw_linkedin": "PM building integrations and automation products at Zapier. Five years in SaaS working on the connective tissue between apps \u2014 integrations, APIs, workflow automation. Remote-first since the beginning of my career. Based in Edinburgh. I love building products that developers trust and that make non-technical users feel powerful. Looking for Senior or Lead PM roles in B2B workflow or integration platforms.", "raw_interview_transcript": "Interviewer: Marcus, thanks for joining. You have a strong integrations background. How does B2B workflow automation translate to procurement software?\n\nMarcus: Procurement workflows are fundamentally about connecting people, approvals, and data across systems. That's the same problem I've been solving at Zapier \u2014 how do you move information reliably between systems without breaking or losing context? I think there's strong overlap.\n\nInterviewer: This role does involve managing junior PMs. You're coming from an IC PM background \u2014 how do you feel about taking on direct reports?\n\nMarcus: I'd welcome it. I've been an informal mentor to two associate PMs at Zapier and I've enjoyed that. I'm ready for the formal step. I'd want to be thoughtful about onboarding \u2014 I know managing people is a different skill from being a great IC PM.\n\nInterviewer: The role is fully remote. You're based in Edinburgh?\n\nMarcus: Yes, I've been fully remote since I joined Zapier. Edinburgh is home and I'm very settled here. Async-first culture suits me very well.\n\nInterviewer: Experience with B2B enterprise sales partnership?\n\nMarcus: Some \u2014 at Zapier I worked with 20+ integration partners and some had enterprise licensing discussions. But direct enterprise customer sales partnership is lighter in my background compared to, say, a PM at a sales-led company.\n\nInterviewer: Salary?\n\nMarcus: I'm on \u00a378,000. Looking for \u00a385\u201390,000 for a senior role with management responsibility.", "years_experience": 5.0, "skills": ["Product strategy", "API products", "integrations", "developer experience", "Amplitude", "Jira", "Figma", "SQL (basic)", "roadmapping", "workflow automation", "B2B SaaS", "integrations marketplace strategy"], "industries": ["SaaS", "Integrations & Automation", "Developer Tools", "Procurement Software"], "seniority_level": "senior", "management_experience": true, "education_level": "bachelor", "career_trajectory": "ascending", "interview_score": 0.82, "culture_fit_score": 0.78, "constraints": [{"id": "4970af15", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Current salary: \u00a378,000 (stated in interview transcript)", "canonical_key": "salary_min", "value": 78000.0, "operator": "min", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.97, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "30d1e688", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Seeking minimum \u00a385,000 for senior role with management responsibility (stated in interview transcript)", "canonical_key": "salary_min", "value": 85000.0, "operator": "min", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.96, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "2d926945", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Upper salary expectation \u00a390,000 for senior PM role (stated in interview transcript)", "canonical_key": "salary_max", "value": 90000.0, "operator": "max", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.95, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "781f5725", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "location", "description": "Requires fully remote working; has been fully remote since joining Zapier (stated in interview transcript)", "canonical_key": "remote_ok", "value": true, "operator": "requires", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.97, "currency": null}, {"id": "215f709d", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "location", "description": "Based in Edinburgh, UK; very settled there (stated in interview transcript and CV)", "canonical_key": "location_city", "value": "Edinburgh", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.92, "currency": null}, {"id": "0c106dcc", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "work_arrangement", "description": "Strong preference for async-first working culture (stated in interview transcript)", "canonical_key": null, "value": "async-first culture", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.88, "currency": null}, {"id": "3e8894a9", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "visa", "description": "British citizen; no visa sponsorship required (stated in CV)", "canonical_key": "visa_sponsorship", "value": false, "operator": "excludes", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.98, "currency": null}, {"id": "629b2c04", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "role_type", "description": "A